CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1780582264
OL,3,CWhy this week's rain is so important
OL,4,Cand how to make the most of it for
OL,5,Csummer
OL,7,FThe amount of water collected depends
OL,8,Fon the size of the roof and rainfall,
OL,9,Fbut you might be surprised how quickly
OL,10,Fa modest downpour can top up a water
OL,11,Fbutt connected to a home's guttering.
OL,13,FFor gardeners, stored rainwater can
OL,14,Fprovide a valuable reserve during dry
OL,15,Fspells as it reduces the need to use
OL,16,Fdrinking water on plants and lawns.
OL,18,FIn fact, rainwater is naturally softer
OL,19,Fthan tap water and is well suited to
OL,20,Fflowers, vegetables and container
OL,21,Fplants.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
